org.jscsi.parser

Class InitiatorMessageParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jscsi.parser.AbstractMessageParser
      • org.jscsi.parser.InitiatorMessageParser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataOutParser, LoginRequestParser, LogoutRequestParser, NOPOutParser, SCSICommandParser, SNACKRequestParser, TaskManagementFunctionRequestParser, TextRequestParser

    public abstract class InitiatorMessageParser
extends AbstractMessageParser

    InitiatorMessageParser

    This abstract class is the base class of all initiator message parsers defined in the iSCSI Protocol (RFC3720). This class defines some methods, which are common in all parsers to simplify the parsing process.

    Author:
    Volker Wildi

    • Field Detail

      • commandSequenceNumber

        protected int commandSequenceNumber
        Command Sequence Number.

        Enables ordered delivery across multiple connections in a single session.

      • expectedStatusSequenceNumber

        protected int expectedStatusSequenceNumber
        Expected Status Sequence Number.

        Command responses up to expectedStatusSequenceNumber - 1 (mod 2**32) have been received (acknowledges status) on the connection.
